comments.body:
@TomSweeneyRedHat (I also haven't looked deeply yet).  IIUC, the main difference here is the underlying environment (setup by automation elsewhere), and that they're all very high-level tests.

No I don't think these should run for every PR, they should run around the time of packaging and maybe periodically as well.

I'll take a look in more depth this afternoon or Tuesday morning.

@ypu how are you doing here?  Having working system-tests is becoming pretty urgent, is this PR close?  Can it be simplified down to just the functional changes?   

I hate to suggest, but should we think about re-opening my old python-based system tests?  Not ideal, but they did work, and could be foundation to grow on.

Background: There's an ask to make RHEL builds block on podman system-tests.  We absolutely cannot do that without working system-tests :smile:

> I really don't like the idea to close this pullreq

Me neither, let's try hardest to get this working (even at basic level).  Additional improvement can be made on top/later.

@rhatdan rodger-dodger, will give it a poke as-is...

@ypu I blame @edsantiago :grin: I just tried `make system.test-binary` and it did the right thing.

/lgtm

@lsm5 so it's even easier to package now, just make sure `$GOPATH` is set, and run that command.  Package up `system.test` in an appropriate directory for a test binary, and that's it!  There's a `test/README.md` that can serve as (imperfect) documentation - if that's ok, otherwise we can skip that for now.
